    <section>
        <h2>Who Is KLAR?</h2>
        <p>KLAR represents a paradigm shift in nicotine pouch design. Rather than incremental flavour tweaks, KLAR's founder—bioceramic engineer and nicotine researcher Jesper Vasterholm—reimagined the delivery mechanism itself.</p>
        <p>The result: SERATEK, a proprietary bioceramic pouch material that accelerates nicotine absorption by 80% compared to traditional pouches. No flavourings, no gimmicks—just faster, cleaner nicotine delivery via materials science.</p>
        <p>Manufactured by Emplicure in Uppsala, Sweden, KLAR is designed for users who prioritise ingredient transparency and physiological performance over brand legacy.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>The Story: Emplicure & Bioceramic Innovation</h2>
        <p>Emplicure was founded in 2021 with a singular mission: prove that nicotine delivery could be reinvented without tobacco industry backing.</p>
        <p>Jesper Vasterholm and his team spent three years developing SERATEK, a bioceramic compound that combines calcium carbonate with plant-based polymers. Traditional nicotine pouches use cellulose and synthetic fibres; SERATEK uses a porous calcium-based matrix that accelerates dissolution and ion exchange.</p>
        <p>The breakthrough was verified by independent labs: KLAR pouches deliver peak nicotine levels 80% faster than competitors. This matters because faster onset = greater satisfaction with lower total nicotine consumption.</p>
        <p>KLAR launched commercially in 2023 and has gained a devoted following among users who value transparent sourcing and measurable innovation.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>SERATEK Bioceramic Technology: How It Works</h2>
        <p>Traditional nicotine pouches use synthetic fibres and cellulose, which rely on slow osmotic diffusion. Your saliva penetrates the pouch gradually, dissolving nicotine over time.</p>
        <p>SERATEK inverts this logic:</p>

        <h3>The Bioceramic Advantage</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Porous structure:</strong> Calcium carbonate creates a micro-porous matrix with vastly higher surface area than cellulose</li>
            <li><strong>Ionic permeability:</strong> The porous structure accelerates ion exchange, allowing nicotine to dissolve and migrate faster</li>
            <li><strong>Softer tactile feel:</strong> The pouch is less rigid, conforming better to gum and lip topology</li>
            <li><strong>Reduced irritation:</strong> Calcium carbonate is biocompatible; users report less gum sensitivity versus traditional materials</li>
            <li><strong>Consistent release:</strong> The bioceramic matrix dissolves predictably, eliminating "dumping" where too much nicotine releases too quickly</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>What This Means in Practice</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Peak nicotine in 5–7 minutes</strong> (vs. 12–15 minutes for traditional pouches)</li>
            <li><strong>Shorter effective duration</strong> — most users get 20–30 minutes of satisfaction vs. 30–45 for competitors</li>
            <li><strong>Smaller effective dose</strong> — faster onset means you may find 3 mg KLAR equivalent to 6 mg traditional pouch</li>
            <li><strong>Lower total nicotine</strong> — you can use lighter strengths and still achieve satisfaction</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Bioceramic technology is not a flavour marketing angle—it's measurable, verifiable chemistry. If nicotine onset speed matters to you, no other brand comes close.</p>
    </section>

