    <section>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <h3>1. Is bioceramic technology safe?</h3>
        <p>Yes. Calcium carbonate is food-grade and biocompatible (used in antacids, supplements, food additives). The polymer matrix is plant-derived and inert. KLAR pouches meet all UK nicotine pouch safety standards and carry no additional risk compared to traditional pouches. Independent labs have verified material safety. That said, nicotine itself is addictive—the materials are safe, but the substance is not risk-free.</p>

        <h3>2. Why is KLAR more expensive than other brands?</h3>
        <p>Bioceramic manufacturing is more complex than traditional pouch production. Emplicure invests heavily in R&D and quality control. Additionally, KLAR has smaller market share, so economies of scale don't apply yet. You're paying for verified innovation, not just brand markup. As KLAR scales, prices may decrease.</p>

        <h3>3. How much shorter is KLAR's duration compared to other pouches?</h3>
        <p>Typically 20–30 minutes for KLAR vs. 30–45 minutes for traditional pouches. This varies by individual metabolism and pouch strength. Most users find KLAR's rapid onset compensates for shorter duration—peak satisfaction is achieved faster, even if total session is shorter.</p>

        <h3>4. Can I mix KLAR with traditional pouches throughout the day?</h3>
        <p>Yes, absolutely. Many users do: KLAR for rapid morning/afternoon hits, traditional pouches for longer evening sessions. Mix and match based on your schedule. Just monitor total daily nicotine to avoid excessive consumption.</p>

        <h3>5. Is KLAR available in strengths below 3 mg?</h3>
        <p>Not currently. KLAR's 3 mg (Regular Mini Mint) is the lightest option. However, due to bioceramic acceleration, 3 mg KLAR delivers equivalent satisfaction to 5–6 mg traditional. If you're very light user, KLAR 3mg Blank (unflavoured) may feel less intense than Mint. Start there and increase if needed.</p>
